The paper discusses challenges and opportunities in the design of scalable wireless systems to manage big data traffic in wireless networks. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories in computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on wireless communication networks, cs.NI is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.IT for signal processing techniques, cs.DS for data management, cs.DB for database design, and cs.MM for multimedia applications.
